<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  [%- PROCESS config.tt -%]
  [%- title = "Getting Started" -%]  
  [%- INCLUDE header.tt -%]
  
  <body>

    <!-- HEADER -->
    <div id="header_wrap" class="outer">
        <header class="inner">
          <h1 id="project_title">[% title %]</h1>
          [%- INCLUDE nav.tt -%]
        </header>
    </div>

    <!-- MAIN CONTENT -->
    <div id="main_content_wrap" class="outer">
      <section id="main_content" class="inner">
        <h2>Requirements</h2>

        <ul>
          <li>Graal requires Java 7 or newer.</li>
          <li>Download <a href="[% './' _ config.graalVersion _ '/graal-' _
          config.graalVersion _ '-for-example0.jar' %]">Graal</a> (this
          package contains the core, homomorphism, backward_chaining,
          forward_chaining, io-dlgp, store-rdbms modules and their dependencies)</li>
          <li>Download <a href="dl/examples/Example0.java">Example0.java</a></li>
          <li>Download <a href="dl/resources/animals.dlp">animals.dlp</a></li>
        </ul>

        
        <h2>Build</h2>

        <p>Open a terminal and go to the folder where downloaded
        files are. Then, execute the command below:</p>

        <pre><code>javac -cp .:./graal-[% config.graalVersion %]-for-example0.jar Example0.java</code></pre>

        <p>Alternatively, you can download the <a href="dl/examples/Example0.class">pre-compiled
          version</a>.</p>

        
        <h2>Run the example</h2>

        <p>Execute this command:</p>
        <code>java -cp .:./graal-[% config.graalVersion %]-for-example0.jar Example0 animals.dlp</code>

        <h2>What does this example do?</h2>
        <ol>
          <li>Create a relational database store with HSQLDB (An
            InMemory Java database system),</li>
          <li>Parse Animals.dlp (A <em>Dlgp</em> file with rules and
            facts),</li>
          <li>Print the set of rules in <em>Dlgp</em>,</li>
          <li>Print the set of facts in <em>Dlgp</em>,</li>
          <li>Parse a query from the code and print it,</li>
          <li>Query the store without reasoning,</li>
          <li>Backward chaining,</li>
          <li>Forward chaining.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>To continue</h2>

        <p>More examples are available <a href="https://github.com/graphik-team/graal/tree/master/graal-examples/src/main/java/fr/lirmm/graphik/graal/examples">here</a> and will soon be
        discuss here.</p>
 
      </section>
    </div>

    [%- INCLUDE footer.tt -%]

  </body>
</html>
